--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Name   : resolver
Type   : ansible role
Group  : sys-core

Authors: liv community
License: Simplified BSD License

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages resolver.

The resolver configuration file contains information that is read by the
resolver routines the first time they are invoked by a process. The file is
designed to be human readable and contains a list of keywords with values that
provide various types of resolver information.
The configuration file is considered a trusted source of DNS information
(e.g., DNSSEC AD-bit information will be returned unmodified from this source).

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: resolver
    vars:
      resolver_state: 'install'
      resolver_domain: 'domain.tld'
      resolver_nameserver: [{server: {'192.168.1.11', '192.168.1.12'},
                             comment: 'Server: domain.tld'}]
      resolver_search: ['domain01.tld', 'domain02.tld']

DISABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: resolver
    vars:
      resolver_state: 'disable'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: resolver
    vars:
      resolver_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  resolver_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
                 'resolv.conf' is a core file and can therefore not be removed.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

  resolver_domain
    Description: Define the 'resolver_domain' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : "{{ansible_domain}}"
    Options    :
      Examples: 'domain.tld' | 'example.tld'
      None    : ''

  resolver_nameserver
    Description: Define the 'resolver_nameserver' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array/Hash
    Default    : [{server: {'127.0.0.1'},
                   comment: 'Server: Localhost'}]
    Options    :
      Examples: [{server: {'192.168.1.11', '192.168.1.12'}, comment: 'Server: domain.tld'}] |
                [{server: {'192.168.1.21'}, comment: 'Server: Nameserver 01'},
                 {server: {'192.168.1.22'}, comment: 'Server: Nameserver 02'}]
      None    : []

  resolver_search
    Description: Define the 'resolver_search' option.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array
    Default    : ["{{ansible_domain}}"]
    Options    :
      Examples: ['domain.tld'] | ['domain01.tld', 'domain02.tld'] |
                ['domain01.tld', 'domain02.tld', 'domain03.tld']
      None    : []

  resolver_resolv_conf_template
    Description: Define the template source for 'resolv.conf.j2'.
                 Any value other than "{{ansible_os_family}}" requires a Jinja2
                 file to be created. The custom Jinja2 file for an example
                 configuration called 'example' needs to be placed as follows:
                 'resolver/templates/example/resolv.conf.j2'
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : "{{ansible_os_family}}"
    Options    :
      Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'

